@node requirements "Requirements"

                               Requirements
                               ------------

Workbench 2.04 (V37) or higher.

T: assigned. - for temporary files.

Reqtools.Library by Nico Francois in LIBS: - distributed in archive.

DFB.Library V1.0 or higher by Andrew Leppard in LIBS: - Distributed with
                                                        DFB

The Join command in C:      --. Both are distributed with Workbench
The Delete command in C:    --' by Commodore or Amiga Technologies

DFB-FLG.config in the programs current directory.

At least 2MB of RAM recommended.

@endnode

@node gadgets "Gadgets"
                                  Gadgets
                                  -------

CheckMark Gadgets
-----------------
           
These are pretty obvious! :))

Filename:       - Enable/Disable Filenames in the generated FileList.
Filesize:       - Enable/Disable Filesizes in the generated FileList.
Description:    - Enable/Disable Descriptions in the generated FileList.
Section #:      - Enable/Disable the inclusion of the DFB sections numbers as
                  part of the information on the generated FileList .
Uploader:       - Enable/Disable the inclusion of the Uploaders name.
Alias:          - Enable/Disable the inclusion of the Uploaders Alias (where 
                  applicable).
Separator Bar:  - When enabled a bar is placed between files, when disbabled
                  2 blank lines are placed between files.
Header:         - Include a textfile at the start of the generated FileList
                  (Registered Users Only)
Guide Button    - Decides on whether to generate an AmigaGuide file with
                  small or large buttons.

e.g.

Large
-----

 @{"20 Text Files" LINK hmmmmm}

Small
-----
 
 @{" * " LINK Hmmmmm} 20 Text Files



Button Gadgets
--------------

About           - About the program! :)
Ascii List      - Generate an Unsorted ASCII List (Less Memory Intensive)
Sorted List     - Generate a Sorted ASCII List (ie all files in any
                  particular section are kept together)  :)
AmigaGuide List - Generate an AmigaGuide FileList!
Greetz          - Some Greetings!
Quit            - Guess! :))

@endnode

@node config "Configuring DFB-FLG"

                              Making a Config
                              ---------------

For DFB-FLG to know what you want your sections to be called you must
create a text file containing the section numbers and the names you want to
give. Those without a name will have 'Section XX - No name' in the final
list.

The config is just a matter of creating a text file with the section number
followed by a space character followed by the description. Each section
must be on a new line as follows. The config must be called DFB-FLG.config
and placed in the same directory as the DFB-FLG main executable.

An example config:

1 MODS - TV/Film
2 MODS - Games
3 BBS - MAXS/PARAGON
4 MODS - Songs
5 Sound Samples
6 BBS Misc
7 Disk Utils
8 Anti - Virus
9 Pictures - Sci-Fi
